# diskarte-site — build-time public configuration.
#
# Copy to `.env` for local review. Everything here is PUBLIC by definition:
# Astro inlines PUBLIC_* values into the static output, so no secret may ever
# be placed in this file or in `.env`.

# Base URL of the Diskarte acquisition service that accepts alpha waitlist
# signups (POST <base>/v1/waitlist, JSON {"email":"…"}, always 202 for a
# well-formed address). The full contract path is also accepted verbatim.
#
# Leave unset/empty and the signup form renders its honest "alpha signup opens
# shortly" state — the site never shows a form that quietly drops addresses.
#
# In CI this comes from the GitHub Actions repository *variable* of the same
# name (Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions → Variables), not a secret:
# this repo is secretless by design (ADR 0045 §5).
PUBLIC_DISKARTE_WAITLIST_URL=
